&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17320548" author="aholmber" created="Tue, 13 Apr 2021 21:49:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As shown in the error in the description,  we&apos;re occasionally bumping into coordinator timeouts, which are &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/6665fc29b33abcc26aad4cecbfee88225b0a7225/test/distributed/org/apache/cassandra/distributed/upgrade/MixedModeAvailabilityTestBase.java#L64-L65&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;set to a smaller value&lt;/a&gt; by the test. I assume they were set lower to make the test timeout faster when we are &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/6665fc29b33abcc26aad4cecbfee88225b0a7225/test/distributed/org/apache/cassandra/distributed/upgrade/MixedModeAvailabilityTestBase.java#L113&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;expecting a failure&lt;/a&gt;. However, simply raising them then causes the test to occasionally fail in a different way (&lt;tt&gt;Failure&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;Timeout&lt;/tt&gt;) if the node shutdown occurs mid-request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m pushing a potential patch that makes sure the coordinator sees the node as down, then expects an &lt;tt&gt;UnavailableException&lt;/tt&gt;. I&apos;m not sure if/why the &lt;tt&gt;Timeout&lt;/tt&gt; exception would be essential to this test, but if that is preferred we could look at another technique of inducing the timeout deterministically without making it cause flakiness.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/aholmberg/cassandra/pull/54&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/aholmberg/cassandra?branch=CASSANDRA-16586&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;ci&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17320637" author="aholmber" created="Wed, 14 Apr 2021 01:54:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CI says I broke the other availability upgrade tests, so sitting on this until I can get back into it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17324024" author="aholmber" created="Fri, 16 Apr 2021 18:50:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I ran into trouble getting the shutdown approach working with some of the earlier versions. Instead I pushed a simplified version that&lt;br/&gt;
1.) extends the request timeout by a second to get away from false negatives&lt;br/&gt;
2.) uses message filtering to effect timeouts to nodes when &quot;down&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test run &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/aholmberg/cassandra/250/workflows/c139a296-8b51-4e33-881f-ff811dbec0d3/jobs/2998/parallel-runs/0?filterBy=ALL&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17325419" author="edimitrova" created="Tue, 20 Apr 2021 02:20:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One nit, otherwise LGTM, thanks!&lt;br/&gt;
We need second reviewer, maybe &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=adelapena&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;adelapena&quot;&gt;adelapena&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dcapwell&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dcapwell&quot;&gt;dcapwell&lt;/a&gt; will volunteer? Does anyone of you have a bit of time?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17325918" author="blerer" created="Tue, 20 Apr 2021 15:48:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch look good to me.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
